FBIS3-1965 "drchi042_o_94012" FBIS-CHI-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 REGIONAL AFFAIRS East Region Zhejiang's Hangzhou Strives To Attract More Tourists OW0203093794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0752 GMT 2 Mar 94 OW0203093794 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Hangzhou, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Hangzhou, one of China's tourist meccas, in Zhejiang Province, is striving to improve its facilities and attract more tourists this year. An official in charge of tourism said that the city will speed up the transformation of the old urban districts, introduce international conventions and add more cultural attractions this year. Famous for its picturesque Western Lake, Hangzhou received 199,800 overseas tourists last year, an increase of 8.7 percent over the previous year. The proportion of foreign tourists rose from 37.54 percent of the total number of tourists in 1992 to 43.46 percent last year. With a history of 2,100 years, Hangzhou has 49 sq [square] km of scenic spots.
